A novel from Wu Zhi Ci Ming
In a beautifully lush and green forest with tall
foliage, the noise of insects resounded amidst the
silent night. The moonlight shone through small spots
on a the thick canopy, infusing it with an enchanting
atmosphere. However, the tranquility was broken by the
rustling sound of grass and leaves being stepped on as
a figure ran through the forest. The figure clutched
their right shoulder as they ran.
Someone trailed behind, holding a sword, seemingly
chasing the escaping figure. "Do you think you can
outrun me?" The pursuer brandished his sword, executing
a series of fluid swings through the air, and
whistlings sound echos. The escaping figure quickly
sidestepped but a few cut wounds appeared on his back
as he let out a grunt.
This guy is cooking hold up!
*I emersed myself in the book for the next hour*
